| none || none&lt;ref name=&quot;FishFish1996StudentsGuide&quot;&gt;{{cite book|last=Fish|first=J.D.|coauthors=Fish, S.|title=A student's guide to the seashore|year=1996|edition=2|pages=418–419|chapter=Bryozoa|isbn=0521468191|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge}}&lt;/ref&gt; (except in family [[Eleidae]]&lt;ref&gt;{{cite journal|last1=Jablonski|first1=D.|last2=Lidgard|first2=S.|last3=Taylor|first3=P.D.|year=1997|title=Comparative Ecology of Bryozoan Radiations: Origin of novelties in cyclostomes and Cheilostomes|journal=[[Palaios]]|publisher=Society for Sedimentary Geology|volume=12|pages=505–523|doi=10.2307/3515408|url=http://jstor.org/stable/3515408|issue=6}}&lt;/ref&gt;) || None in most species || Yes (except in genus ''[[Bugula]]'')
